Let's start by merging the square roots:

$\begin{align}
\sqrt{z}\cdot\sqrt{30z^2}\cdot\sqrt{35z^3}&=\sqrt{z\cdot 30z^2\cdot 35z^3}
\\\\
&=\sqrt{1050z^6}
\end{align}$

Now we remove all perfect squares from inside the square root:

$\begin{align}
\sqrt{1050z^6}&=\sqrt{5^2\cdot 2\cdot 3 \cdot 7\cdot \left(z^3\right)^2}
\\\\
&=\sqrt{5^2}\cdot\sqrt{42}\cdot\sqrt{ \left(z^3\right)^2}
\\\\
&=5\cdot \sqrt{42}\cdot z^3
\\\\
&=5z^3\sqrt{42}
\end{align}$

