Let's start by merging the square roots:

$\begin{align}
\sqrt{2a}\cdot\sqrt{14a^3}\cdot\sqrt{5a}
&=\sqrt{2a\cdot 14a^3\cdot 5a}
\\\\
&=\sqrt{140a^5}
\end{align}$

Now we remove all perfect squares from inside the square root:

$\begin{align}
